HEADWORD: magnetic pole
<hw>magnetic pole</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Either of two
points where the lines of force of the earth's magnetic field are
vertical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the two ends of a magnet where the magnetic
field is strongest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>magnetic recorder</ent>⟦br⟧
